,Not Recommended,433380,34158505,Posted: 10 August,all,Samuel,"As a person who's watched Joe Gran's YouTube channel for a long time, one of the characters that has stood out to me the most has been 90's Nick, because I come across his archetype quite often in online circles.This feels like if that character made a throwback game. It's not a good game by any stretch of the word, but it nails down the feeling and aesthetics of mid-to-late 90's PS1 poly aesthetics (which I can admit are quite likable!). That being said, the combat is boring, there's very little differentiation between enemy types, and the game is super easy as you'll be able to hoard painkillers as you complete mundane task after mundane task. I got a good amount of the achievements in far under an hour, which isn't really appealing since the game itself cost me $11.99. If you're looking for something to itch your Silent Hill scratch, you're probably just better off playing an emulated version of Silent Hill 2 or 3.3/10"
