,Recommended,433380,30228183,Posted: 27 February,all,BoneDaddyDiesel,"Honestly, the game isn't very challenging nor is it very long. You can complete the entire game in about 2 hours. But I'm not here to destroy this game, I actually quite enjoyed it. For what it's worth, 1995 is a very quaint and compelling spin on the old school survival horror games. It is very reminiscent of Silent Hill and does a good job of making you feel the nostalgia and the sense of mystery that the old games did. The notes tell the story and give you a feel for what's going on in this world. A few surprises here and there, along with some basic back tracking and puzzles to get the gears turning. The price is a little steep for the game as-is (DLC is apparently scheduled to come soon), so if you can get this when it's on sale I say it's worth it. If you take your time and really go through and read everything and explore all the areas the game has to offer I feel you mostly get your money's worth. I give it a solid 7.5/10!"
